I can show basics of our code for using the built-in encoders for drivetrain distance. You’ll have to adapt it to your elevator parameters.

Setting: left_leader = new CANSparkMax(RobotMap.left_leader_id, MotorType.kBrushless); leftEncoder = left_leader.getEncoder();

public static final double conversionFactorP = wheelDiameterMeters * Math.PI * gearRatio;

leftEncoder.setPositionConversionFactor(Constants.conversionFactorP);

Using: leftEnc = Robot.drivetrain.getLeftEncoder(); private double curDistFeet() { return Units.metersToFeet(leftEnc.getPosition() + rightEnc.getPosition()) / 2.0; }
